&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re leading the way in redefining the workwear category. Our mission is to engineer better boots and apparel for our country’s tradesmen and women by working directly with real workers to learn what they actually need to execute their jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The BRUNT team is not only devoted to improving on the old workwear standards, but we’re also creating a community that tradesmen and women can call their own. From our weekly hangouts at the BRUNT Garage, to hosting events across the country, we’re all about getting boots on the ground and building something real with the BRUNT crew.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is responsible for overseeing daily operations of BRUNT’s 3PL network while driving efficiency, accuracy, scalability, and cost-effectiveness as the business grows. Reporting to the Senior Director of Operations, you will work closely with internal and external partners to optimize BRUNT’s outbound distribution, returns management, and inventory accuracy across DTC, wholesale, and retail channels. This role will play a critical part in scaling BRUNT’s distribution capabilities as wholesale and retail become larger parts of the business, while also supporting the evaluation and launch of a second warehouse location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will leverage deep warehouse management, 3PL management, and omnichannel distribution expertise to position BRUNT for seamless expansion, enhancing distribution capabilities as we scale across DTC, wholesale, retail, and future distribution locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role means BRUNT’s distribution network operates with best-in-class speed, accuracy, cost control, and scalability. You will ensure our 3PL partners consistently hit SLA expectations, inventory remains accurate and available, returns are processed efficiently, wholesale partners receive compliant and on-time shipments, and the business has clear visibility into distribution performance as we expand into additional locations and channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You’ll Do It:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Warehouse Operations Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and optimize 3PL warehouse operations and distribution activities across all locations, ensuring SLA compliance, inventory accuracy, and cost efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the day-to-day relationship with BRUNT’s 3PL, providing timely and consistent communication while holding them accountable for all KPIs and SLAs across, Outbound Distribution, Inventory Management, and returns management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own core distribution KPIs, including on-time ship performance, order accuracy, inventory accuracy, dock-to-stock timing, click to ship, return processing time, refurbishment recovery, cost per order, and cost per unit shipped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement strategies to optimize storage and distribution processes to improve efficiency and reduce costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement initiatives through the implementation of best practices, technology advancements, and data-driven decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the quarterly business review process with our 3PL partners, including performance scorecards, action plans, and continuous improvement opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with 3PL to ensure inventory control measures are in place, including cycle counting, reconciliation processes, root cause analysis, and corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate receipt forecasts, product launches, channel demand, promotional calendars, and seasonal peaks into warehouse capacity plans, ensuring 3PL partners have the labor, space, equipment, and operational readiness needed to support BRUNT’s growth.&lt;/li&gt;
